Miso Ginger Chicken Slaw
  --Holly Erickson & Natalie Mortimer
  
3 tbsp white or yellow miso paste
2/3 c vegetable oil
3 tbsp unfiltered apple cider vinegar
3/4 tsp sea salt
1 1/2 tsp sesame oil (toasted or untoasted)
1 tbsp honey
1 1/2 tsp grated ginger
2 garlic cloves, minced
3 c cooked shredded chicken
3/4 c sliced almonds, toasted
1/2 c chopped cilantro leaves
3 c shredded green or Napa cabbage (from 1 head)
3 c shredded red cabbage (from 1 head)
2 large carrots, julienned
4 green onions, chopped
fried shallots, for serving (optional)

In a blender or food processor, combine the miso, vegetable oil, vinegar, salt, sesame oil, honey, ginger, garlic, and 3 tbsp of water. Blend until smooth. In a large bowl, combine the chicken, almonds, cilantro, green cabbage, red cabbage, carrots, and green onions. Drizzle with the dressing and toss to combine. Sprinkle with the fried shallots if using and serve immediately. 
